The paper discusses information retrieval and ranking of Wikipedia articles, which falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The use of PageRank and CheiRank algorithms for ranking the articles also suggests the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The analysis of categories such as countries, universities, personalities, etc. indicates the use of data mining and machine learning techniques, which could fall under the sub-categories of Digital Libraries (cs.DL) and Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). Finally, the paper also discusses the properties of the ranking system, which could be relevant to the sub-category of Social Computing (cs.SOC).
